cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL 

This paper focuses on improving semantic segmentation for urban-scene images using a novel attention mechanism. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new module for improving segmentation, which involves training a neural network, making it likely to fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the unique characteristics of urban-scene images, which could place it under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper discusses the interpretation of the attention map, which could place it under cs.CL (Computation and Language).
